WEBVTT

00:00:58.720 --> 00:01:01.134
in terms of how engaged he was
in the conversation.

00:01:01.158 --> 00:01:03.143
Shalina: I met with a venture capitalist,

00:01:03.167 --> 00:01:07.424
and during our meal, I put a chocolate
dessert ball in my mouth,

00:01:07.448 --> 00:01:09.280
only to later find out

00:01:09.304 --> 00:01:15.971
that it was actually part of his extremely
expensive ancient marble art collection.

00:01:15.995 --> 00:01:19.816
AG: Networking can be forced,
cringe-worthy or worse.

00:01:20.162 --> 00:01:22.053
But it doesn't have to be that way.

00:01:22.077 --> 00:01:25.196
(Theme music)

00:01:28.704 --> 00:01:32.362
I'm Adam Grant, and this is WorkLife,
my podcast with TED.